# 56f4a2bb4d814e209d36cd609439881b
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:4
msgid "Session Protocol"
msgstr ""

# 4a409a63827a4acbb5cfd0439c1f155d
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:23
msgid ""
"Traffic Server supports some session level protocols in place of, or on "
"top of HTTP. These can be provided by a plugin (see :ref:`new-protocol-"
"plugins`) or be one that is supported directly by Traffic Server. The "
"`SPDY <http://www.chromium.org/spdy>`_ protocol is the only one currently"
" supported, but it is planned to support HTTP 2 when that is finalized."
msgstr ""

# d2094005c7e74e638584d0c463f551fd
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:29
msgid ""
"Session protocols are specified by explicit names, based on the `NPN "
"<https://technotes.googlecode.com/git/nextprotoneg.html>`_ names. The "
"core supported names are:"
msgstr ""

# c5a698a83c3142d0844fce22832401bd
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:33
msgid "``http/0.9``"
msgstr ""

# 56ac01d2df734aa799416dae450da62b
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:34
msgid "``http/1.0``"
msgstr ""

# 59ed36f7ec644188914ae5244561a858
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:35
msgid "``http/1.1``"
msgstr ""

# b5daf0fa86a04360a65b3763cd278f1b
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:36
msgid "``http/2``"
msgstr ""

# ec90af0fbe7c49da83bda45ad409f1d9
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:37
msgid "``spdy/1``"
msgstr ""

# 64d62b5d71d345d483a59a0877fdf1b0
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:38
msgid "``spdy/2``"
msgstr ""

# 9e7422726c014fbebcb5672868b332ce
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:39
msgid "``spdy/3``"
msgstr ""

# 37ee111d57724ba7aaa6522cbadb8895
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:40
msgid "``spdy/3.1``"
msgstr ""

# 9835f3ac37394f58bb1430058d5978de
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:42
msgid ""
"The ``http/2`` value is not currently functional, but is included for "
"future use. Both ``spdy/1`` and ``spdy/2`` are obsolete, but are include "
"for completeness."
msgstr ""

# 9c6edbd35a554633b70cd7fbcb9e1a45
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:46
msgid ""
"The session protocols supported on a proxy port are a subset of these "
"values. For convenience some pseudo-values are defined in terms of these "
"fundamental protocols:"
msgstr ""

# 93f28d0214394c48bdfa4b30172920e9
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:50
msgid "``http`` means ``http/0.9``, ``http/1.0``, and ``http/1.1``"
msgstr ""

# a8ccdd5427224608b4dba5f865087e4c
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:51
msgid "``spdy`` means ``spdy/3`` and ``spdy/3.1``."
msgstr ""

# 1332c268d27c445c9070d5e807385fdf
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:52
msgid "``http2`` means ``http/2``"
msgstr ""

# 9225b6999ec248a4be083b8f7246688d
#: ../../admin-guide/configuration/session-protocol.en.rst:54
msgid ""
"Each proxy port can be configured in "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.server_ports` to support a subset of these "
"session protocols. For TLS enabled connections this configuration "
"controls which protocols are offered by NPN. Protocol sniffing is use for"
" non-TLS proxy ports to determine which protocol is being used by the "
"client. If the detected protocol is not supported for that proxy port the"
" connection is dropped."
msgstr ""

